Interface NetworkListener

  • All Known Implementing Classes:
    Accumulator_fragment, Accumulator_view_activity, Checklist_fragment, Checklist_view_activity, ChecklistElement_view_activity, Dashboard_activity, Dashboard_fragment, Drone_fragment, Drone_view_activity, Flights_fragment, Flights_view_activity, Forgot_password_activity, Login_activity, Login_settings_activity, Register_activity, Settings_dashboard_activity, User_fragment, User_view_activity

    public interface NetworkListener
    The network listener to listen to events from the network. You will alos get the results of a request as event.

    • Method Detail

      • requestWasSuccessful

        void requestWasSuccessful(List<Map<String,String>> results,
                          String message,
                          String requestIdentificationTag)
        This method is called from the NetworkHandler when the current request of the NetworkThread finished successfully.
        Parameters:
        results - The results from the request in a List of Maps. Each Map represents an object in the data array received from the web server.
        message - The message send from the web server.
        requestIdentificationTag - The identification tag of the specific request type. With this value you can identify the request type. Look public static variables in subclasses of Request to compare values.

      • sessionHasExpired

        void sessionHasExpired(String message,
                       String requestIdentificationTag)
        This method is called from the NetworkHandler when the current request of the NetworkThread was redirected and the user has to log in again.
        Parameters:
        message - The message send from the web server.
        requestIdentificationTag - The identification tag of the specific request type. With this value you can identify the request type. Look public static variables in subclasses of Request to compare values.

      • exceptionOccurredDuringRequest

        void exceptionOccurredDuringRequest(Exception e,
                                    String message,
                                    String requestIdentificationTag)
        This method is called from the NetworkHandler when an exception occurred during the current request.
        Parameters:
        e - The exception instance.
        message - The message send from the web server. If no message exists this value is null.
        requestIdentificationTag - The identification tag of the specific request type. With this value you can identify the request type. Look public static variables in subclasses of Request to compare values.
